{
  "stem": "9730.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We fought in World War I and some of us died, and they will never do anything really drastic to us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I personally was not quite that optimistic in the time immediately before Hitler's rise to power.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And after that, of course, we were to find out that each day or each week brought new decrees that made our life harder.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I'll tell you one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In March of 1933-- Hitler came to power in January of '33.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I came home from school one time, and- and I see that there are two stormtroopers, SA men, standing guard in front of our house.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I wasn't quite sure whether they would let me through, but they apparently knew me, and did let me through.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But this was the day in which the Nazis began their infamous boycott of Jewish homes and businesses.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was-- it was geared to keep the populace from doing business with or being friendly with Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that-- that was their overt demonstration of-- of how they would keep the people from associating with Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And from then on in, things got progressively worse.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were, of course, the Nuremberg Laws, which followed in '35, and-- in-- in which Jews were removed from all official positions, anything to do with schools, universities, the medical establishment insofar as it was municipal.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] so there were all sorts of restrictions like that, where people couldn't keep their jobs.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And also, businesses were already feeling the pinch, Jewish businesses, because the boycott had its effect, of course, in that non-Jews didn't-- bought-- bought from Jews in-- in lesser numbers, although it didn't completely dry up yet.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
